This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with single-view object reconstruction using convolutional networks. It also involves image classification and retrieval, which are subfields of computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically encoder-decoder networks, which are commonly used in deep learning and fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). 

The paper discusses the idea of non-trivial reasoning about 3D structure, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper also involves graphics and visualization, as it deals with 3D reconstruction and the output space, which are topics in computer graphics (cs.GR). 

Finally, the paper involves multimedia, as it deals with image classification and retrieval, which are subfields of multimedia (cs.MM).
